<subSubSection id="C30644A7FFBA1B50F6BCFA589B79D3FB" pageId="6" pageNumber="311" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA3172CFFBA1B50F6BCFA589B79D3FB" blockId="6.[151,1437,1374,1941]" pageId="6" pageNumber="311">
<emphasis id="B968CB3EFFBA1B50F6BCFA589ED3D34E" bold="true" box="[199,408,1518,1544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="311">Diagnosis (Male).</emphasis>
Antenna filiform, first antennomere shorter or slightly longer than third antennomere (
<figureCitation id="13270BA9FFBA1B50F314FA599FF6D36B" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1804,1828]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,184,1780]" captionTargetId="figure-21@7.[151,1436,181,1780]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Embolemus ruddii Westwood, 1833, holotype, male from United Kingdom, (OUMNH). A. Body, dorsal view; B. Fore wing; C–E. Head; C. Frontal view; D. Lateral view; E. Dorsal view; F, I. Mesosoma; F. Dorsal view; I. Lateral view; G. Metapectal-propodeal complex, dorsal view; H, J. Metasoma; H. Dorsal view; J. Lateral view; K. Holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559821/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="311">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); head swollen in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="13270BA9FFBA1B50F46DF9A59D21D36B" box="[534,618,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1804,1828]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,184,1780]" captionTargetId="figure-21@7.[151,1436,181,1780]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Embolemus ruddii Westwood, 1833, holotype, male from United Kingdom, (OUMNH). A. Body, dorsal view; B. Fore wing; C–E. Head; C. Frontal view; D. Lateral view; E. Dorsal view; F, I. Mesosoma; F. Dorsal view; I. Lateral view; G. Metapectal-propodeal complex, dorsal view; H, J. Metasoma; H. Dorsal view; J. Lateral view; K. Holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559821/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="311">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
); face with two convergent longitudinal and median sutures from clypeus to antennal toruli; ocelli distinct (
<figureCitation id="13270BA9FFBA1B50F469F9819D27D317" box="[530,620,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1804,1828]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,184,1780]" captionTargetId="figure-21@7.[151,1436,181,1780]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Embolemus ruddii Westwood, 1833, holotype, male from United Kingdom, (OUMNH). A. Body, dorsal view; B. Fore wing; C–E. Head; C. Frontal view; D. Lateral view; E. Dorsal view; F, I. Mesosoma; F. Dorsal view; I. Lateral view; G. Metapectal-propodeal complex, dorsal view; H, J. Metasoma; H. Dorsal view; J. Lateral view; K. Holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559821/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="311">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); labial 2 or 3-palpomeres (
<figureCitation id="13270BA9FFBA1B50F5DCF9819B4BD317" box="[935,1024,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1804,1828]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,184,1780]" captionTargetId="figure-21@7.[151,1436,181,1780]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Embolemus ruddii Westwood, 1833, holotype, male from United Kingdom, (OUMNH). A. Body, dorsal view; B. Fore wing; C–E. Head; C. Frontal view; D. Lateral view; E. Dorsal view; F, I. Mesosoma; F. Dorsal view; I. Lateral view; G. Metapectal-propodeal complex, dorsal view; H, J. Metasoma; H. Dorsal view; J. Lateral view; K. Holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559821/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="311">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); maxillary 4 or 6-palpomeres, third maxillary palpomere broadened (
<figureCitation id="13270BA9FFBA1B50F473F9ED9D2BD333" box="[520,608,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1804,1828]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,184,1780]" captionTargetId="figure-21@7.[151,1436,181,1780]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Embolemus ruddii Westwood, 1833, holotype, male from United Kingdom, (OUMNH). A. Body, dorsal view; B. Fore wing; C–E. Head; C. Frontal view; D. Lateral view; E. Dorsal view; F, I. Mesosoma; F. Dorsal view; I. Lateral view; G. Metapectal-propodeal complex, dorsal view; H, J. Metasoma; H. Dorsal view; J. Lateral view; K. Holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559821/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="311">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); macropterous, fore wing usually with Costal (C), Radial (R), first cubital (1Cu), and first medial (1M) cells enclosed by pigmented veins, second cubital (2Cu) cell almost always open, first medial (1M) cell occasionally open (
<figureCitation id="13270BA9FFBA1B50F448F9159DC0D3FB" box="[563,651,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1804,1828]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,184,1780]" captionTargetId="figure-21@7.[151,1436,181,1780]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Embolemus ruddii Westwood, 1833, holotype, male from United Kingdom, (OUMNH). A. Body, dorsal view; B. Fore wing; C–E. Head; C. Frontal view; D. Lateral view; E. Dorsal view; F, I. Mesosoma; F. Dorsal view; I. Lateral view; G. Metapectal-propodeal complex, dorsal view; H, J. Metasoma; H. Dorsal view; J. Lateral view; K. Holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559821/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="311">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
); tibial spurs formula 1/2/2 (
<figureCitation id="13270BA9FFBA1B50F5B0F9159B6ED3FB" box="[971,1061,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1804,1828]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,184,1780]" captionTargetId="figure-21@7.[151,1436,181,1780]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Embolemus ruddii Westwood, 1833, holotype, male from United Kingdom, (OUMNH). A. Body, dorsal view; B. Fore wing; C–E. Head; C. Frontal view; D. Lateral view; E. Dorsal view; F, I. Mesosoma; F. Dorsal view; I. Lateral view; G. Metapectal-propodeal complex, dorsal view; H, J. Metasoma; H. Dorsal view; J. Lateral view; K. Holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559821/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="311">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
